The paper deals with a problem of performing set-difference range queries, which involves geometric ranges and set-theoretic symmetric differences. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of computer science that deal with data structures (cs.DS), databases (cs.DB), computational geometry (cs.CG), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Among these, cs.DS and cs.DB are the most likely categories, as the paper deals with data structures and sketches for solving set-difference range queries.
